name: Titan
description:
Titan is a symbol of the dome of the sky and a symbol of the breadth and height of nature.
Titan or Titan (the name of one of the races of the gods in Greek mythology) The children of the mother earth (Gaia) and the father of heaven (Uranus) were the first creatures in which the traces of life were.
According to the ancient Greeks, these were immortal and powerful gods who saved human life in battle with demons, and the survival of the earth owes much to the efforts of the Titans.
